response.Q0: I saw that the cost of inspecting the nodes was low, so I didn't pay much attention to it. From my inspection, I noticed that $88 was probably the maximum I could earn at the final nodes. So my strategy was to pick a maximum of 5 nodes to inspect, If I found a node that was worth between $55-$88 before inspecting the fifth node then I'd head straight for the highest node, regardless of what the cost was.
response.Q1: Yes, initially I didn't know what was the maximum I could earn for a final node, so I picked randomly and chose whatever node had a positive value. As time went on, I noticed the maximum value I could earn on the final nodes, so I made sure to pick a final node that was close to the maximum value.
